    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The shift position sensor is fixed to the transmission control shaft. The control shaft rotates via the control wires when the driver operates the select lever. The shift position indicator shows which position is selected using a LO/HI signal based on the angle of rotation of the control shaft. In addition to operating the shift position sensor, the control shaft also switches the transmission hydraulics between forward, neutral, and reverse by operating a manual valve. The PGM-FI ECU uses the signal from the shift position sensor to determine the gear shift schedule. The input terminal voltage of the PGM-FI ECU is HI when each switch in the shift position sensor is open and LO when closed. When a shift position signal different from the shift position signal selected by the select lever is input at the same time, The PGM-FI ECU determines a failure and stores the DTC."
    },
