    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Failure Criteria"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If any of the following is established"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "When a position signal input other than the signal input selected with the select lever continues for more than 1 second at the same time. (FWD position signal input [forward SW] is excluded)"
        },
        {
          "text": "P, R or N position signal input [AT P, R or N SW] and simultaneously FWD position signal input [FORWARD SW] continues for more than 1 second."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Estimated Failure Site"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Short circuit in the cord between the PGM-FI ECU and the shift position sensor (each switch line)"
        },
        {
          "text": "Shift position sensor failure"
        },
        {
          "text": "PGM-FI ECU internal circuit failure"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Reproducibility Testing Methodology"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Start the engine."
        },
        {
          "text": "With the brake pedal depressed, hold all select lever positions for at least 1 second in each position."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "None."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to be faulty, the D indicator light flashes without the PGM-FI warning light illuminating, and the temporary DTC, DTC and freeze data are stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use of the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or removal of the 12V battery terminal will clear the D indicator light, temporary DTC, DTC, and freeze data."
    }
